Conventions
-----------
* classes must be named name.class.php
  * every additional class need to extend AccessibleObject
    to be able to check its (method) parameters first
  * define no constructors for those classes 
* test classes are named name.test.class.php
* szenario tests can be created using phpunits testsuites
* preamble for setting up include_path to be able to load classes using relative
  pathes from root
* placeholders in configuration or source files will be replaced 
  during deploy/test runs or whenever needed
  * e.g. @php-deploy-path@
  * have a look at build.xml, especially the last targets
* using namespaces (for external classes)
  * http://stackoverflow.com/questions/32478962
  * namespaced class files within other namespaces need to be called
    with root namespace prefix
    * \util\sth\Class replaces util\sth\Class if namespace is not
      util\sth
* test files
  * class file [Cc]lass[Nn]ame.class.php
  * corresponding testfile [Cc]lass[Nn]ame[Tt]est.test.class.php
* logging
  * extend LoggableObject to pin logging functionality onto objects
    * avoids file handle and resource corruption upon (de)serialization
  * use $this->logger to log messages

Testing
